1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,560
What evidence, Mr. Yai?

2
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:27,480
I suspect that my dad might not have died
from illness, Uncle Pload.

3
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:30,520
I would never think
of betraying you, Madam.

4
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:33,200
Then kill Yai for me. Can you do that?

5
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,760
Please welcome Mr. Yai, Chalit,
the only heir to Paisal Farm,

6
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:40,320
and Pinanong, the beautiful bride.

7
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,760
You never fail to give me what I want.

8
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,600
Don't forget what we agreed.

9
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,600
You look so beautiful today, Pin.

10
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:29,120
So beautiful that you're melting
the heart of every man here…

11
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:37,040
me included.

12
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:43,920
Loose-lipped,
throwing around empty flattery,

13
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,160
it won't work on Pin.

14
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:49,600
Right, honey?

15
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,480
Pin and I

16
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,800
have so many fond memories together.

17
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:24,080
You will need to try your best

18
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,520
to erase them.

19
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,560
I'm rooting for you.

20
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,520
It won't be that hard.

21
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:05,920
Pin.

22
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,440
Aunt Un's not home.
I don't know where she is.

23
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,320
We can go pay respects to her later.

24
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,440
Aunt Un.

25
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,840
I'm so glad you came.

26
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,400
You're still my daughter.

27
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:01,440
May this holy water open your eyes…

28
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:08,240
so you don't see others

29
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:10,840
as superior to the one who raised you

30
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,720
and fed you.

31
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,680
- Thank you.
- Congratulations, Pin.

32
00:07:08,760 --> 00:07:10,680
- You look gorgeous.
- Thank you so much.

33
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,600
Thank you.

34
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,840
Let's take more photos.

35
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:16,080
- Follow us.
- I'll be right there.

36
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,280
Pin, are you tired?

37
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,040
I'll go get you a drink.

38
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:23,800
Okay.

39
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:29,040
Our beautiful bride.

40
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:32,360
You must be exhausted right now. Here.

41
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,440
I brought you some water.

42
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,200
Thank you so much, Ms. Nee.

43
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,800
Don't drink it yet.

44
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,440
Let's make a toast first.

45
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:46,760
I wish my beautiful Pin

46
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:51,120
a torturous marriage
with her groom forever.

47
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:52,720
Cheers!

48
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:59,000
Sorry, I didn't mean to do that.

49
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:00,720
Just consider it

50
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:04,200
practice before facing
real violence and abuse tonight, okay?

51
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:06,480
Because you'll be facing

52
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:09,040
something a hundred times
more painful tonight.

53
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:12,920
Prepare to be kicked around
by a mad thief like Mr. Yai.

54
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,080
You might have forgotten

55
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:17,800
that Mr. Yai and I
have spent the night together.

56
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:21,400
Mr. Yai was incredibly gentle.

57
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:24,320
That's why this wedding has happened.

58
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:25,720
Please don't worry about me.

59
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,080
Stop right there!

60
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:33,640
I know that you've been planning
to get with Mr. Yai all along.

61
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:37,240
You even used your body
to climb up to my level.

62
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:39,720
But a lapdog like you,

63
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:42,480
even if you were to become
an arrogant madam

64
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:44,720
with a neck full of diamonds,

65
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,640
every time I called your name,

66
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,480
you'd still have to rush
to be at my feet, you servant!

67
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:55,880
I've always known my place
as a maid's daughter.

68
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:59,120
I don't have a high status like you have,

69
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,920
but I've never looked down
on other people.

70
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,360
I've never stepped on others to make
myself higher like you're doing now.

71
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,840
Big mouth, huh, Pin?

72
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,120
I'm sorry.

73
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,760
I was going to give you a drink,

74
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:16,760
but I tripped over myself.

75
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:18,360
It spilled everywhere.

76
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,080
You…

77
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,160
I'm so clumsy!

78
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,720
You two just wait.

79
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,760
I'll get back at you someday!

80
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,320
Pretty but such a nasty mouth.

81
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,480
She's been terrible since childhood.

82
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:39,720
No one taught her any manners, huh?

83
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:46,160
Forget her. She's just pitiful.

84
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:50,760
Oh, Jin.

85
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:53,440
Where did Jom go, exactly?

86
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,840
Has anyone found him?

87
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:10,640
Jom? Jom.

88
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,240
Pin?

89
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,800
Are you going to run away with me now?

90
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:23,680
No one's running away.

91
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:25,880
Get up. Go sleep at your house.

92
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,800
No.

93
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:32,520
I won't let you
go through hell living with Yai.

94
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,960
Pin.

95
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,120
I love you, Pin.

96
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,400
Run away with me.

97
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:46,400
I'll take care of you. Okay, Pin?

98
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,960
- Let's go.
- Jom, let go of me. Jom!

99
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,520
- Pin.
- Let go, Jom.

100
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,600
You can't even stand up by yourself.

101
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:58,320
How are you supposed to take care of her?

102
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:02,240
If you keep acting foolish like this,

103
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,920
even without Mr. Yai there,

104
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,760
Pin still wouldn't be interested in you.

105
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:13,440
No… That's not true… That's not true…

106
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:17,680
That's not true… Pin…

107
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:31,280
Please run away with me…

108
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:33,360
Run together…

109
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:37,280
Run away with me…

110
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,800
Jan told me today

111
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:47,040
that the bandit, your brother,

112
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:49,400
had a big makeover
and became handsome, right?

113
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,080
The workers were showing off pictures.

114
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,760
Na.

115
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,040
Na.

116
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:09,320
Yes, On?

117
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:13,960
What are you looking at?

118
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:17,920
It's nothing.

119
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,480
I was just checking my friends' texts

120
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:22,160
to see if any of them came home.

121
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:24,480
Are your friends girls?

122
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:27,920
Come on, On.

123
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,520
Who else would I be interested in

124
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:33,680
other than my On?

125
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:39,600
I only have you too.

126
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:42,560
I left everything behind

127
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:46,960
and had to endure
these trashy people just for you.

128
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:51,000
If you betrayed me,
I would never forgive you.

129
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,520
Come on, On.

130
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,440
What are you saying?

131
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,880
That isn't going to happen.

132
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:04,800
Tomorrow, let's go to Bangkok

133
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:07,240
to prepare for our wedding.

134
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:09,600
I don't want to stay here anymore.

135
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:11,760
Okay.

136
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,960
And once you sell the farm,

137
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,560
let's go to Australia.

138
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:19,680
I really want a penthouse in Sydney.

139
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,960
Okay, On.

140
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,760
And I want a villa on the Gold Coast too.

141
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:27,640
I just want to sunbathe all day.

142
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:59,880
Just a few sweet words from him
and you get swayed.

143
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,280
How pitiful.

144
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:03,320
You're just as good at deceiving me.

145
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,560
We're not the same.

146
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:06,640
I made it obvious
that I'm the number one bad guy,

147
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,640
not a fake gentleman like him.

148
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:10,960
Just give me back my stuff.

149
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:12,840
You're married to me now.

150
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,320
Why would you keep your ex's stuff?

151
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:15,840
Still haven't moved on from him?

152
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:19,480
I married you. Why are you still jealous?

153
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:21,680
Or are you insecure about yourself?

154
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:25,760
Are you trying to provoke me? Fine.

155
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,200
I'm easily provoked.

156
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:29,040
I'll burn this to a crisp.

157
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:32,080
No, Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai, just give it back.

158
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,120
If you want it, come get it.

159
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,520
Give it back.

160
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:38,200
Mr. Yai, give me back my stuff.

161
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:42,320
- This is not funny.
- Wait, wait. Calm down. Pin, easy.

162
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,720
Are you trying to pin me down?

163
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,080
Give it back.

164
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,560
Help! My wife is trying
to ravish me! Help!

165
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:49,960
- Mr. Yai, give it back.
- Wait, wait.

166
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,200
You want it so much?

167
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,120
Come get it yourself, then.

168
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,040
Hey, wait, Pin. Hey.

169
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,720
Are you really gonna take off my pants?

170
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:04,760
From now on, I won't be
the only one getting picked on.

171
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:08,840
I'm going to put you
out of commission for good.

172
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:11,520
You little kitty.

173
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,320
I can break your arm with one twist.

174
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,400
Don't threaten me.

175
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:21,800
What are you gonna do?

176
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:36,200
Perhaps

177
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,920
Waan and Noi forgot to remove the thorns.

178
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:43,520
They're perfectly sharp and spiky.

179
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,160
Just one scratch

180
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:48,240
and you'd definitely bleed.

181
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:51,520
Pin, don't fool around like this.

182
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:52,960
It's dangerous. I could end up sterile.

183
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,960
- No, Pin. Pin.
- Come here.

184
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:57,280
- Give the notebook back.
- Wait, Pin. Hold on.

185
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:59,560
- Give it back.
- Pin.

186
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:01,000
- Don’t come any closer.
- Stop right there.

187
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,120
- Mr. Yai.
- You wanna play like this?

188
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,360
Have some of this, Boss.

189
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,000
That's enough.

190
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:08,360
To Yai. Everyone, cheers!

191
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,640
Yeah!

192
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,640
- Come on.
- Yes.

193
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,160
Pload.

194
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:22,200
If Mr. Yai hadn't let me
talk to you that day,

195
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:24,920
I would have kept believing
he was a thief.

196
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:29,240
So everything you've been doing
has just been to deceive Madam?

197
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:35,800
I want to find out the truth
about Pha's death.

198
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,360
I'll have you talk with someone.

199
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,320
Uncle Pload.

200
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:52,560
I want you to tell Uncle Win
about our plan.

201
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:56,800
Hello.

202
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,560
Pload?

203
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:04,280
If Mr. Yai hadn't run into me,

204
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,800
he would have lost his way by now.

205
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:09,319
His true self

206
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:11,720
is quite gullible.

207
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,119
He easily trusts people.

208
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,560
Are you talking about Pin?

209
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,119
Yes.

210
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:31,960
Pin is a good girl, Pload. I assure you.

211
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:33,920
Regardless,

212
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:37,280
Pinanong and her mom
are under that madam's influence.

213
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:39,440
Mr. Yai marrying Pinanong

214
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:42,280
is like keeping
a venomous snake by his side.

215
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:50,400
Tawin, you have to promise me

216
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:53,560
that you'll be our eyes and ears.

217
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:56,320
- Alright?
- Yes.

218
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:02,520
Help!

219
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:03,760
- Hey.
- Mr. Yai.

220
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:05,680
- Mr. Yai.
- Go. Now.

221
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:09,800
Mr. Yai.

222
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:11,320
I knew this would happen.

223
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,880
Hey, break the lock and get in.

224
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,280
- Yes.
- Hurry.

225
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:21,480
- Mr. Yai.
- Help! Help me!

226
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:22,680
Help!

227
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:30,720
I was being too rough, Uncle Pload.

228
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,240
Holy moly, Mr. Yai.

229
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:35,360
You're this strong
on the first night, huh?

230
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,320
Yai, stay still.

231
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:41,400
Let me go live to let everyone know

232
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:43,840
with the caption
"The honeymoon was going great

233
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,280
until the bed gave out."

234
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:49,880
Pan. If you don't want me
to kick you in the neck, stop filming.

235
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,840
No filming. Don't film me.

236
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:54,000
Uncle Pload. Look at him.

237
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:55,160
Stop it now.

238
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,920
That's enough. Guys, let's go.

239
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,800
If nothing's happening, let's just go.

240
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,760
What are you filming? Back off, Pan.

241
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:02,720
Pan.

242
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,520
Yes, Dad. It's just a joke.

243
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,720
Mr. Yai. Does it hurt much?

244
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:17,080
Because of you,
I feel totally embarrassed.

245
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,280
Because of me?

246
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,440
Don't you ever think
something is your fault for once?

247
00:19:21,520 --> 00:19:22,760
See now?

248
00:19:22,840 --> 00:19:25,640
What goes around comes around.

249
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:30,480
Uh, Pin. Where are you going?

250
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:32,720
Then where am I supposed to sleep?

251
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:36,840
Just you wait.

252
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:39,480
There's more than just one wedding night.

253
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:46,080
Pin. Pin.

254
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,360
Good mor…

255
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:12,360
Auntie. Have you seen Ms. Pin?

256
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:13,440
I did.

257
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:16,280
I saw her walking down there
with a notebook.

258
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:24,040
You love that stupid Indian cork tree
so much? I'll burn it down.

259
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:44,960
From now on,

260
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:48,040
I won't be able
to think about you anymore, Mr. Na.

261
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:27,760
<i>We're moving in to seize the area.</i>

262
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,320
What is it?

263
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,600
Don't you know what time it is?

264
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:43,080
Don't you have any manners?

265
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:51,400
Mr. Yai gave me the order,

266
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:53,160
so I have to execute it right away.

267
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,360
Noi. Waan. Proceed.

268
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,440
- Yes.
- Yes.

269
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,360
Excuse me.

270
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:01,000
Excuse us, Ms. On.

271
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:04,200
What's all this noise about?

272
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:12,680
Stop right now.

273
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,040
Why are you messing with my stuff?

274
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:24,240
Stop right there. Stop.

275
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:27,000
I won't let you take it away.

276
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:28,920
You lowlife. Let go of my stuff.

277
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,920
- You let go of it, Ms. On.
- Let go.

278
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,600
- Ms. On.
- Na, don't just stand there. Help me.

279
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,640
I'm warning you.

280
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:38,960
Think before you do anything, Mr. Tatsana.

281
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:41,040
- On. On.
- Let go of it!

282
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:42,320
- Ms. On.
- On.

283
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:44,400
Let them take your stuff for now.

284
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:46,200
I'll go negotiate with Mr. Yai.

285
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:50,520
I won't negotiate anything with them.

286
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,360
I have to get my stuff back. Let go!

287
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,040
Ms. On, you're the one
who needs to let go.

288
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,960
- I said let go.
- Ms. On!

289
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:59,320
- Ms. On!
- Are you not gonna let go?

290
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,680
Hey.

291
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:05,680
Jan, they're taking away my belongings.

292
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:07,680
Those are my clothes. Get them back.

293
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:08,760
Give it to me, Noi.

294
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,640
Give it here. Give it.

295
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:11,760
- Let go.
- You let go!

296
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:13,000
Hey.

297
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:15,680
We have hands and feet too, you know?

298
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:21,160
Ms. On, let go.

299
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:22,640
Why are you taking it? Give it back!

300
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:25,800
- Why are you taking it? Why?
- Ms. On.

301
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:26,840
- Let go.
- Give it.

302
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:28,720
I said give it back!

303
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:29,680
Hey!

304
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,560
What is happening here?! I'm sleeping.

305
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:42,840
Auntie, Mr. Yai suddenly sent someone
to chase me out of my bedroom.

306
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:44,400
He's clearly bullying me.

307
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:46,680
I won't let this go, Auntie.

308
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,280
This is too much.

309
00:23:49,360 --> 00:23:51,360
Na has been sleeping
in that room since he was little.

310
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,160
We have so many cabins in the resort.

311
00:23:53,240 --> 00:23:54,760
Just pick one.

312
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:57,080
You must have forgotten

313
00:23:57,160 --> 00:23:59,240
that before I left this place,

314
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,120
that room belonged to me.

315
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:05,040
Now that I'm back,
Tatsana has to hand it back to me.

316
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:06,160
Isn't that right?

317
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:13,440
The rightful owner of this place is Na.

318
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:16,760
Auntie, go get the will
and show it to him!

319
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:18,160
- So we can settle this.
- Yeah, good idea!

320
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:19,960
Let's see that will you're talking about.

321
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,960
I want to see too

322
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:24,520
if my dad really gave
this place to Tatsana.

323
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:27,880
If he did,
I'll leave this farm in style for you all.

324
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:42,800
Hey, I never thought these
high-society types would hit so hard.

325
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,960
Yeah. Jan was no pushover either.

326
00:24:45,040 --> 00:24:47,000
If she wasn't so old,

327
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:48,600
I'd slap her eyes out.

328
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:49,640
- Good.
- Yeah.

329
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:52,280
Mr. Yai.

330
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:55,960
Which cabin should we bring these bags to?

331
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:59,000
It's up to them.

332
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:00,560
Let them pick their place.

333
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:02,800
- That's rough.
- That's rough.

334
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,840
I'm sorry, Auntie,
for causing you trouble.

335
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:11,040
I should be the one thanking you

336
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:14,000
for not kicking me
and my niblings out of the farm.

337
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:19,680
No need to walk me.

338
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:23,960
Go take care of On

339
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:27,440
and warn her about what I told you.

340
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:36,120
Yes.

341
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,480
Where are you going, Madam?

342
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:46,000
You can stop calling me madam.

343
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:49,800
Because from now on,
you're the madam of the Paisal house.

344
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:53,240
I'm the one who has to rely on your power.

345
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,320
If I have ever upset you,

346
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,800
please forgive me.

347
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,400
It's good that you said that.

348
00:26:04,840 --> 00:26:06,240
Moving forward,

349
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:08,960
you'll be overseeing
all the farm's properties.

350
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:12,800
You're the one who holds
all the keys of Paisal Farm.

351
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:14,200
You can order anyone to do anything.

352
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:28,000
All she says is
to wait for the court order.

353
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:29,960
I'm starting to wonder

354
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,600
if your aunt is hiding something

355
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,680
since she let Yai bully her so much,

356
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,640
even making her move out of the house.

357
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:40,960
Well, as Auntie said,

358
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:44,560
if we had brought the will out now,
Mr. Yai would have just burned it.

359
00:26:45,360 --> 00:26:49,520
On, you yourself saw how Mr. Yai is.

360
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:51,360
Please wait a little longer.

361
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:55,200
How long? I have no time left, Na.

362
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,600
No time left for what?

363
00:26:57,680 --> 00:26:59,600
Your mother
hasn't even sent the auspicious date.

364
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:08,240
Well… Uh…

365
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:11,600
I'm afraid. I'm afraid that

366
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:14,000
if she finds out that
there's a problem at your farm,

367
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:17,440
she might no longer want me to marry you.

368
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:21,080
Na.

369
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,960
Let's have our wedding in Bangkok soon.

370
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:26,440
No need to wait
for the auspicious date anymore.

371
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:29,480
I don't want to stay here any longer.

372
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:30,360
Please.

373
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:34,400
Agreed, Miss. In this day and age,
no one cares about auspicious dates.

374
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:37,520
You can even fix bad luck later.

375
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:40,920
But we need to leave this place
as soon as possible.

376
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,720
You can scold me all you want, Pin.

377
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:53,680
What? I'm not allowed
to touch your sweetheart's family?

378
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:57,640
I don't want anyone to say you're cruel.

379
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:07,800
Let them say it. Do I need to care?

380
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:10,600
Mr. Yai.

381
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,160
We're like the same person now.

382
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:16,920
An insult to you is an insult to me.

383
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,360
I don't want to hear any of that.

384
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:21,080
Technically, we're still different people.

385
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:23,880
Then, shall we do it tonight? Let's merge.

386
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,000
You said it yourself that
we're the same person.

387
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:32,960
I meant that we're married.

388
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:35,760
Let's start over.

389
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:38,320
Forget all the grudges
between you and Madam.

390
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:41,520
Start by giving up this house,
and let's go stay where we were.

391
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:43,880
Let them see how generous you are.

392
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:51,320
You want me to be nice
so I can get picked on like you did?

393
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,640
That's definitely not me.

394
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:57,040
You can just be
a good, obedient wife for me.

395
00:28:58,240 --> 00:29:01,400
Then how can this place be peaceful?

396
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:03,280
Well? It's not that hard.

397
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:06,120
If anyone steps out of line,
just take them out and end it.

398
00:29:06,200 --> 00:29:07,440
Mr. Yai.

399
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:10,560
Can we talk honestly for once?

400
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:20,280
Fine. I'll be honest with you.

401
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:25,120
Everything I've done
has been to try to protect your dignity.

402
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:27,760
Do you like it
when people call you a servant

403
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:29,880
or call you names?

404
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:33,360
You've always been picked on,
and then you cried alone.

405
00:29:37,280 --> 00:29:40,040
They had to do this
because they feared you.

406
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:41,760
Should I be happy about that?

407
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:43,640
I've told you before.

408
00:29:43,720 --> 00:29:46,920
People worship the rich
because of their money.

409
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:49,120
They don't care if that millionaire

410
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,160
is self-made or just a thief.

411
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:08,120
Have a safe journey, Uncle.

412
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:11,040
Please tell Aunt Pen that
as soon as I'm done here at the farm,

413
00:30:11,120 --> 00:30:12,200
I'll bring my wife to visit.

414
00:30:12,800 --> 00:30:14,480
Yes, Mr. Yai.

415
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:20,480
You're married to her,
but you still can't trust her.

416
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:26,240
I really want you to rest assured

417
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:28,280
that Pin isn't Madam Krongsuk's pawn.

418
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:32,440
She even returned
all the farm keys I gave her.

419
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:34,600
Then don't forget the promise

420
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:36,360
you made to me.

421
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:43,600
- Good luck, Mr. Yai.
- Yes.

422
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,760
Let's go, guys. Let's start our trip home.

423
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,720
Hey. You're a grown man now.

424
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:52,160
We don't need to hug, Pan.

425
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:53,640
What, Dad?

426
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,680
But you hugged Yai.

427
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:57,240
That's such a double standard.

428
00:30:59,320 --> 00:31:00,840
Good luck, Son.

429
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:05,160
- Safe trip, Dad.
- Good luck.

430
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:25,120
Come here. I'll hug you myself.

431
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:27,280
Hey, Yai. Knock it off.

432
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:30,560
People will see us. Go hug your wife.

433
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:32,120
Ugh, that gives me the creeps.

434
00:31:32,200 --> 00:31:33,760
Yeah, good idea.

435
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:35,320
Pin has much softer skin than you.

436
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:38,200
Go away, Yai. You love-sick jerk.

437
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,400
Get lost already.

438
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,200
Madam?

439
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,600
Un…

440
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:59,440
How could Pin do this to you?

441
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:02,240
Don't blame her.

442
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:05,800
Your daughter
has probably been brainwashed

443
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:07,160
by Yai into hating me.

444
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:11,720
Madam, you shouldn't have stopped me.

445
00:32:12,280 --> 00:32:13,440
If I had killed him…

446
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:16,520
No. Don't say that.

447
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:20,200
If he hears that, Pin would be in trouble.

448
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:24,520
But I can't stand Pin
being ungrateful to you anymore.

449
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:27,320
I'll cut ties with her.

450
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:28,760
If you do that,

451
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:31,120
Na will be in even more serious trouble.

452
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:40,680
I'm fine with struggling alone.

453
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:44,480
But it breaks my heart
to see Na's life ruined.

454
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:47,960
What did Yai do to Mr. Na, Madam?

455
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:03,800
Mom.

456
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:06,360
What are you even doing here?

457
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:08,440
Your room is in the main house, isn't it?

458
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:11,720
I didn't want it to be like that, Mom.

459
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:14,040
I'll try to convince Mr. Yai again

460
00:33:14,120 --> 00:33:16,240
to let Madam
move back into the main house.

461
00:33:16,760 --> 00:33:19,040
But it'll probably take some time.

462
00:33:21,720 --> 00:33:24,640
If you're sure
you're not going to betray Madam,

463
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:25,960
you have to prove it.

464
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:29,320
Give all your dowry to me.

465
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:33,840
What are you going to do with it?

466
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:36,960
Mr. Na needs money for his wedding
as well as for the dowry.

467
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:38,240
I'll give it to him.

468
00:33:38,840 --> 00:33:39,800
So…

469
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:42,120
Madam told you to ask me?

470
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:43,840
Why do you even need to ask?

471
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:49,720
Or was Yai not really going to give
the dowry to me and did it just for show?

472
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:53,000
Did he just really want
to have you for free?

473
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:58,720
I returned the keys to Mr. Yai

474
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:02,560
because I didn't think
you'd want his money.

475
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:05,720
It's stolen money. It isn't really his.

476
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:08,159
Are you not going to give it to me?

477
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:11,239
Then get out
and don't ever speak to me again. Go.

478
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:13,840
- Get out.
- Mom, wait.

479
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:15,520
- Don't you speak to me again.
- Mom.

480
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:18,600
Mom. Let me explain first.

481
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:20,280
Mom.

482
00:35:18,600 --> 00:35:19,600
You smell so good.

483
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:22,920
Did I wake you up?

484
00:35:23,840 --> 00:35:26,240
Yes. I was having a sweet dream

485
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:28,120
about some curvy girl.

486
00:35:28,720 --> 00:35:30,640
But you ruined my dream.

487
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:31,560
You have to pay for it.

488
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:33,520
- Come here.
- Mr. Yai.

489
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:36,600
No, Mr. Yai. I beg you.

490
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:41,200
You're trembling.

491
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:43,240
You think I'd do something to you?

492
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:45,360
I just want you to lie still,

493
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,360
so I can have a good night's sleep.

494
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:50,120
I have to go to the farm early tomorrow.

495
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:52,320
Come to bed.

496
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:29,600
Why is it taking so long?

497
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,480
Well, Un?

498
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:42,800
How is it going, new madam?

499
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:46,680
You told Mom to ask me
for the dowry, didn't you?

500
00:36:48,720 --> 00:36:51,120
A grateful person like your mom

501
00:36:51,200 --> 00:36:54,920
knows how to repay my kindness
without even being asked.

502
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,440
That's because she loves you so much.

503
00:36:57,520 --> 00:37:00,400
She doesn't care
if what you do is right or wrong,

504
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:02,240
as long as she gets to repay you.

505
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:03,400
That's right.

506
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:07,160
An ungrateful person like you

507
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,120
wouldn't understand.

508
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:17,480
A favor is for others to cherish,
not for the giver to claim, Madam.

509
00:37:17,560 --> 00:37:18,640
Don't lecture me.

510
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:24,320
I'm giving you what you asked for.

511
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:04,640
Mom.

512
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:10,640
I told you
not to show your face here again.

513
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:15,200
Mom.

514
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:18,800
Hey.

515
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,080
Did Madam

516
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:23,000
make you hate me this much?

517
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:24,680
It's because you're
so infatuated with Yai.

518
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:27,640
You're head over heels
and can't see straight.

519
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:30,480
What about you?

520
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:34,640
Do you love Madam so much
that you think she's better than me?

521
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:39,120
Why would you
even compare yourself to Madam?

522
00:38:39,720 --> 00:38:42,360
Well, because sometimes,

523
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:45,360
I feel like you love her more than me.

524
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,960
Listen to me, Pin.

525
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:51,200
She isn't just our master.

526
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:53,920
She's our benefactor, our mother figure.

527
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:56,960
If you won't help her,
it's like you're abandoning me.

528
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:02,920
I gave the dowry to her.

529
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:07,840
Really, Pin?

530
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:13,200
I knew you wouldn't be
an ungrateful person.

531
00:39:16,040 --> 00:39:17,800
You did great, dear.

532
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:23,960
Madam will be happy
and won't be disappointed in you.

533
00:39:26,160 --> 00:39:30,040
Today, I'm making sour soup
with sesbania flowers, Madam's favorite.

534
00:39:30,120 --> 00:39:32,280
I'll serve her in her cabin.

535
00:39:32,360 --> 00:39:34,280
I don't know
if I have all the ingredients.

536
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:36,520
Let's see.

537
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:49,000
I hope this is the last time,

538
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:52,680
so we can finally settle
this debt of gratitude.

539
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:05,000
Mr. Yai.

540
00:40:05,680 --> 00:40:07,960
Your coffee and snacks.

541
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:13,360
Please take a seat right here.

542
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:17,120
- Open up.
- Hey.

543
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:18,800
I'm not disabled.

544
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:22,560
Come on, Mr. Yai.

545
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:26,480
I just want to take good care of you,

546
00:40:26,560 --> 00:40:28,840
so we can grow closer--

547
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:30,800
Hey.

548
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:32,520
Where is everyone else?

549
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:37,520
Na and his fiancée headed out together
earlier this morning.

550
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:39,840
And Pin

551
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:41,560
has disappeared.

552
00:40:41,640 --> 00:40:44,280
Why isn't she staying
to take care of her husband?

553
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:49,920
But it's okay.

554
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:53,960
It's okay, Mr. Yai.

555
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:56,120
You have me right here.

556
00:40:56,200 --> 00:41:00,440
If you want anything,
just request it from me.

557
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:02,400
I'll make it happen.

558
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:10,600
Hey.

559
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:12,400
A tour group is arriving.

560
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:13,600
Go and get ready to receive them.

561
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:16,360
I'm busy.

562
00:41:22,360 --> 00:41:24,920
Yeah! I'm not busy anymore.

563
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,760
Yai, we need to talk.

564
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,520
It can wait. I need to go find my wife.

565
00:41:33,600 --> 00:41:35,360
- She's disappeared.
- No, it's serious.

566
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:36,520
We need to talk now.

567
00:41:42,040 --> 00:41:42,880
Look at what's on this drive.

568
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:46,680
The security camera
you had me install really wasn't a waste.

569
00:43:19,560 --> 00:43:21,600
Why did you close it? That wasn't all.

570
00:43:21,680 --> 00:43:23,920
It's so obvious.
What more do I need to see?

571
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:30,160
Wait a sec.

572
00:43:31,680 --> 00:43:32,760
Hello.

573
00:43:35,160 --> 00:43:36,160
The cafe?

574
00:43:38,600 --> 00:43:39,520
Alright.

575
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:42,520
My informant on the farm called and said

576
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:45,480
that the witch, Teera,

577
00:43:45,560 --> 00:43:49,240
Tsunami, and his elite fiancée
are gathering at the cafe.

578
00:43:51,080 --> 00:43:54,000
It must be about
what Pin stole from the safe.

579
00:44:09,960 --> 00:44:13,000
<i>Mr. Yai got me drunk</i>
<i>and forced himself on me.</i>

580
00:44:13,080 --> 00:44:16,280
You bastard! You have a wife,
but you're still sleeping around!

581
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:17,960
Pin.

582
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:20,400
<i>I'm back, because I missed you.</i>

583
00:44:21,320 --> 00:44:24,120
Add this in, and tell Pin

584
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:25,400
to serve the food to Yai.

585
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:29,080
- Madam.
- I've never feared Madam Krongsuk.

586
00:44:29,160 --> 00:44:30,360
But your mom is a serious problem.

587
00:44:30,440 --> 00:44:32,400
<i>I'll send her somewhere else.</i>

588
00:45:14,320 --> 00:45:16,600
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
